&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Dude Perfect is a leading entertainment brand known for our thrilling sports videos, epic trick&lt;br&gt;shots, and engaging content that resonates with millions of fans around the world. Our team&lt;br&gt;thrives on collaboration, high energy, and bringing people together for unforgettable moments. If&lt;br&gt;you’re passionate about making an impact, love working in a fast-paced environment, and aren’t&lt;br&gt;afraid to bring big ideas to life, we’d love to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for an Editor to support the Dude Perfect’s post-production team. This role will be&lt;br&gt;responsible for assembling, refining, and delivering high-quality edits that capture the energy,&lt;br&gt;adventure, and personality of the channel and the Dude Perfect brand.&lt;br&gt;This is a hands-on role for someone who thrives in fast-paced YouTube production&lt;br&gt;environments. The ideal candidate is comfortable managing full edits independently, from ingest&lt;br&gt;and organization through final delivery. They understand YouTube pacing, unscripted&lt;br&gt;storytelling, and competition-style formats, and can craft compelling and engaging narratives.&lt;br&gt;This role will collaborate closely with Creative Directors, Producers, and the Production&lt;br&gt;Manager to ensure every video meets the highest standard of quality and performance.&lt;br&gt;The Editor will report directly to the Lead Editor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&lt;strong&gt;nitial Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Editorial Execution:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;● Edit compelling sports, spectacle, and outdoor content from first assembly through final&lt;br&gt;delivery.&lt;br&gt;● Shape pacing, tone, and structure to maximize engagement and retention.&lt;br&gt;● Maintain clarity and storytelling continuity across multi-camera and competition-style&lt;br&gt;formats.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;● Partner closely with Creative Directors and Producers to translate concepts into&lt;br&gt;compelling edits.&lt;br&gt;● Incorporate feedback efficiently while meeting delivery timelines.&lt;br&gt;● Communicate proactively about post-production needs and project statuses.&lt;br&gt;Workflow, Quality, and Other&lt;br&gt;● Manage project organization, media ingestion, and file structure.&lt;br&gt;● Maintain adherence to post-production workflows, asset management standards, and&lt;br&gt;style guidelines.&lt;br&gt;● Ensure final deliverables meet technical specifications and platform requirements.&lt;br&gt;● Uphold consistent editorial quality aligned with the Dude Perfect brand and standards.&lt;br&gt;● All other duties as assigned.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;● 3-5+ years of professional editing experience in digital media, sports, entertainment, or&lt;br&gt;high-concept YouTube-first content.&lt;br&gt;● Proven ability to independently manage full edits from ingest through final delivery.&lt;br&gt;● Strong understanding of long-form YouTube pacing, retention mechanics, and audience&lt;br&gt;engagement.&lt;br&gt;● Experience editing unscripted, competition-based content strongly preferred.&lt;br&gt;● Comfort working with multi-camera productions.&lt;br&gt;● Advanced proficiency in industry-standard editing software.&lt;br&gt;● Strong communication skills and ability to give and receive feedback.&lt;br&gt;● Experience working within fast-paced, high-output content teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;● Health, dental, vision insurance&lt;br&gt;● 401(k)&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;● Paid time off &amp;amp; holidays&lt;br&gt;● Unique access to Dude Perfect productions, events, and experiences&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;This position is located onsite at Dude Perfect HQ3 offices in

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dude Perfect is a leading entertainment brand known for our thrilling sports videos, epic trick shots, and engaging content that resonates with millions of fans around the world. Our team thrives on collaboration, high energy, and bringing people together for unforgettable moments. As we continue to grow and scale our team, we’re looking for a resourceful and people-first Human Resources Manager to join our People team and help build the foundation of an incredible employee experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re seeking a Human Resources Manager with strong experience supporting and managing people in retail or high-volume frontline environments, along with a solid understanding of HRIS system implementations and optimization. Reporting to the Head of People, this role will play a critical part in shaping our People Operations function, improving processes, and supporting our leaders and employees as we scale. If you thrive in a fast-moving, values-driven environment and love building structure while maintaining a human touch, this role is for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Initial Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HR Compliance, Policies, Benefit Management &amp;amp; Employee Relations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with federal, state, and local employment laws, as well as internal policies and procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate and organized employee records and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support employee relations matters with professionalism, sound judgment, and a people-centered approach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a point of contact for employee questions regarding benefits, policies, and communications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist the Head of People on company-wide HR strategy, org design, compensation, and communication efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Special Projects - HRIS Implementation &amp;amp; Systems &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead or support implementation, optimization, and maintenance of HRIS platforms (Gusto, Greenhouse, or similar).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as an internal expert for HR systems, ensuring accurate employee data, reporting, and workflow automation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to streamline HR processes and improve efficiency through technology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop documentation, trainings, and resources to help managers and employees use HR systems effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;People Operations &amp;amp; Employee Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a trusted partner for managers and employees, particularly in frontline or customer-facing environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and enhance onboarding and offboarding processes to ensure a smooth and memorable experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage employee lifecycle tasks, including job changes, promotions, documentation, compliance, and policy updates.&lt;br&gt;Support and help lead HR programs such as performance reviews, engagement surveys, development planning, and culture initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide guidance and coaching to managers on people leadership, performance, and team dynamics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4–7+ years of Human Resources experience, with at least 2 years supporting or

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manager, Content Creator Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Frisco, TX&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employment Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-Time&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel Required:&lt;/strong&gt; Yes, potentially 25-50%&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dude Perfect is a leading entertainment brand known for our thrilling sports videos, epic trick shots, and engaging content that resonates with millions of fans around the world. Our team thrives on collaboration, high energy, and bringing people together for unforgettable moments. If you’re passionate about making an impact, love working in a fast-paced environment, and aren’t afraid to bring big ideas to life, we’d love to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dude Perfect is seeking an experienced &lt;strong&gt;Manager, Content Creator Development&lt;/strong&gt; to help source and shape the future on-camera talent in the Dude Perfect ecosystem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is a strong people reader and talent scout who thrives in a creative, fast-paced environment. They have a natural instinct for on-camera presence, chemistry, and audience connection, and they know how to give clear, constructive feedback without stifling creativity. This person is both intuitive and grounded, able to balance creative potential with practical judgment when making talent-based decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Manager, Content Creator Development will initially report directly to Dude Perfect’s Chief Content Officer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and manage the on-camera development pipeline, from early identification through recurring integration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify emerging talent across collaborators, internal creators, and external prospects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead talent testing initiatives, including trial appearances and pilots.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate talent performance based on on-camera presence, chemistry, reliability, and audience response.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide clear, constructive feedback to talent to support growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with producers to shape long-term talent strategy and contributor planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in high-level creative and production conversations to ensure talent decisions align with format needs and brand direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the thoughtful sustainable integration of new talent into the Dude Perfect ecosystem.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;All other duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of progressive experience in talent management, development, and strategy, ideally within entertainment, media, sports, or creator-driven businesses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of on-camera performance and personality-driven content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with creators, performers, and/or talent in a development capacity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to assess creative potential while balancing practical production considerations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable giving direct, actionable feedback in creative environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication, organization, and multitasking abilities under pressure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clear, professional communicator who can give direct, constructive feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with YouTube and creator content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health, dental, vision insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401(k) with employer match eligible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid time off

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dude Perfect is one of the most-watched sports and comedy entertainment brands in the world. From record-breaking trick shots to live tours, original series, games, and consumer products, we build joyful, family-friendly content that reaches a massive global audience. Behind the scenes, our Brand Partnerships team turns that audience into best-in-class sponsorship and integration programs for the world&#39;s leading brands. As we scale, we are building the operational backbone that lets our partnerships business move faster, price smarter, and deliver flawlessly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Sales Operations Manager to own the systems, data, and processes that power our Brand Partnerships engine. This role is the operational center of gravity for the sales team: you will own our CRM, run pricing and deal support, manage our sponsorship inventory, and turn raw sales data into the insights that guide decisions. You will partner closely with sales, marketing, finance, and content teams to keep deals moving and revenue forecastable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is exceptionally detail-oriented, a strong project manager, and a sharp analyst who is energized by bringing order to a fast-moving business. Beyond running the day-to-day, the best version of this person becomes a strategic thought partner to leadership — someone who not only reports what happened, but helps shape what we do next.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CRM &amp;amp; Sales Systems Ownership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own, administer, and continuously improve our CRM (HubSpot) as the single source of truth for the partnerships pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enforce data integrity — clean records, consistent stages, accurate close dates — so forecasts and reporting can be trusted.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain workflows, automations, dashboards, and integrations that reduce manual work for the sales team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pricing &amp;amp; Deal Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and apply our rate cards and pricing models across sponsorship and integration packages, ensuring deals are priced consistently and profitably.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the deal desk: review proposals and contracts for accuracy, pricing alignment, and required approvals before they go out the door.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with finance on margin analysis, discounting guardrails, and revenue recognition inputs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ad &amp;amp; Sponsorship Inventory Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the master view of available sponsorship and ad inventory across content, social, live tours, and other properties — tracking what is open, sold, held, and delivered.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage allocation and availability so the sales team always knows what they can sell, and work to maximize sell-through and monetization of open inventory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with content, production, and marketing to keep inventory data accurate as the calendar and content slate evolve.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reporting &amp;amp; Analytics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain dashboards and reporting on pipeline, bookings, for

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 18pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Director, Marketing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Dude Perfect is a leading entertainment brand known for our thrilling sports videos, epic trick shots, and engaging content that resonates with millions of fans around the world. As we continue to innovate and grow, we’re looking for a strategic marketing leader to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We’re seeking a world-class leader to lead marketing, brand, and communications for one of the most influential YouTube-native media brands in the world. This role is responsible for scaling the business beyond content - launching and growing consumer products, brands, and audience-driven experiences powered by massive global reach. The candidate will blend consumer product marketing, creator economics, and modern marketing technology, translating audience engagement into durable, diversified growth streams. The ideal candidate will be equal parts builder and operator, comfortable in the weeds of a go-to-market campaign one hour and presenting a brand strategy to leadership the next.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Initial Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Launches &amp;amp; Performance Marketing&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead go-to-market strategy for new consumer products, brands, and audience-driven experiences (physical, digital, and experiential)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support product launches end-to-end, including positioning, pricing, demand forecasting, and launch execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support launch and scaling of new YouTube channels, content verticals, and IP-driven franchises, including positioning, audience strategy, and performance optimization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate audience insights into product-market fit, identifying unmet needs and high-conviction opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and optimize acquisition funnels and across owned, earned, and paid channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define growth KPIs and design tracking systems across the full lifecycle (CAC, LTV, conversion, retention, repeat purchase)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design experimentation frameworks for launches, offers, pricing, and messaging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with product, ops, and creative teams to align roadmap, storytelling, and distribution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply an AI-forward lens to marketing operations, leveraging automation and intelligent tooling to maximize efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brand Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead brand strategy for new formats, franchises, products, and spin-off channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define, evolve, and protect the channel’s brand positioning, voice, and narrative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure consistent brand expression across YouTube, social platforms, websites, products, and IRL activations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Anticipate cultural trends, platform shifts, and audience expectations to keep the brand ahead of the curve&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide creative direction in collaboration with content leadership to strengthen brand affinity and loyalty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own public-facing communications and public relations strategy, including press, announcements, and reputation management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead creator, platform, and industry relationships to elevate visibility and influence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee messaging for major launches, partnerships, and moments of cultural relevance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with brand and legal teams on crisis communications and risk mitigation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support shaping executive and creator thought leaders

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Social Content Editor&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dude Perfect isn’t just a YouTube channel, we’re a global sports and entertainment powerhouse. We operate at the absolute peak of digital engagement, with follower growth and view counts that consistently outpace the most iconic sports franchises on earth. From legendary trick shots to massive live tours, we’re in the business of delivering unforgettable moments to a community of over 100 million followers worldwide. We don’t just follow the cultural conversation; we drive it. We’re currently building a world class social media team to redefine what an iconic digital presence looks like.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for the absolute best storytellers in the game: digital natives who are obsessed with creator culture, live for the rush of a viral hook, and have the creative guts to help us build the next era of Dude Perfect across every platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you want to cook the most engaging content with the coolest people for one of the biggest sports and lifestyle brands on the planet… all out of one of the greatest HQs in the world, you’re in the right place. LET’S GO!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dude Perfect is looking for a Social Content Editor to serve as a critical creative engine for our brand partnerships and overall digital presence. This is a role for a pure-play editor who lives at the intersection of high-end VFX and viral short-form strategy. We need an elite editor who is genuinely obsessed with social media and has a passion for crafting content specifically for the vertical frame. You’ll be responsible for turning sponsored integrations into masterpieces, innovating how we hype new releases, and breathing new life into our historical archives for the TikTok and Reels era.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You specialize in transforming both vertical &amp;amp; horizontal footage into platform-native 9x16 masterpieces that satisfy our global brand partners while keeping the DP audience engaged &amp;amp; excited. You’ve spent time in the trenches with top-tier creators, agencies, or pro sports teams, and you know how to maintain an elite level of visual polish under tight deadlines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A vertical and short form editing specialist who deeply understands the trends, pacing, and storytelling required for platform-native success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A technical creative who thrives on bringing long-form cinematic content to a vertical, rapid-fire format.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A master of pacing and emotional beats, able to craft a full, engaging story in under a minute.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proactive collaborator who works seamlessly with the Social Media and Post Production teams from ideation to final publishing.&lt;/li&gt;
